totalcross.lang

Class Array

  • totalcross.lang.Object
    • totalcross.lang.Array
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable

    public class Array
extends totalcross.lang.Object
implements Cloneable
    All arrays extend this class. The purpose is to allow hashCode() and toString() methods on arrays.

    IMPORTANT: the totalcross.lang package is the java.lang that will be used on the device.
    You CANNOT use nor import totalcross.lang package on the desktop. When tc.Deploy is called, all references to java.lang are replaced by totalcross.lang automatically. Given this, you must use only the classes and methods that exists BOTH in java.lang and totalcross.lang. For example, you can't use totalcross.lang.ClassLoader because there is no totalcross.lang.ClassLoader. Another example, you can't use totalcross.lang.String.indexOfIgnoreCase() because there is no totalcross.lang.String.indexOfIgnoreCase() method. Trying to use a class or method from the java.lang package that has no correspondence with totalcross.lang will make the tc.Deploy program to abort, informing where the problem has occurred. A good idea is to always refer to this JavaDoc to know what is and what isn't available.
